Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HashChecker
    Interface for any Classes that perform any hash functions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CliReader
    CLIReader class is responsible for reading user input and making sure it is valid.
    DirReader
    DirReader reads all files in a directory and converts them to a byte array.
    FileByteReader
    FileByteReader class is used to read files and file meta data into a byte array.
    FileControl
    Controls what is added and removed from the hash text file.
    HashControl
    This class is where data gets turned into a hash.
    HashFunction1
    HashFunction1 implements HashChecker as a basis to build the hash function.
    HashFunction2
    HashFunction2 implements HashChecker as a basis to build the hash function.
    HashFunction3
    HashFunction3 implements HashChecker as a basis to build the hash function.
    HashFunction4
    HashFunction4 uses java.security.MessageDigest to use effective real world hashes such as MD5 or SHA-512.
    Main
    Main class where the program starts.
    Menu
    Menu class, this is where all menu actions are called from.
